<p>Please, if I could have your tried and true recipe it would help especially any notations that would help in the process ( the Cordon Bleu seems to assume the chef has some experience in pate making) My sous chef has agreed to help with my endeavor. Luckily for me he has a forgiving palate and will consume my culinary disasters. I get artist's rage and toss it to the dogs or chickens who are less discriminating.</p>
<p>My gut instinct tells me it may not be wise consuming conventionally raised chicken liver. At least, not on a regular basis. The liver would probably be saturated with all the nasty toxic chemicals and antibiotics the poor things were exposed. The FDA has only recently banned arsenic in chicken feed. That they dragged their feet at such a proposal is quite telling.</p>
<p>Miffed;-)</p>

